'''''A Garden of Pomegranates''''' is a 160-page book, written by [[Israel Regardie]] in 1931. The first edition was published in 1932. The book was printed four times, with a second edition being published in 1970 by [[Llewellyn Publications]]. The title pays homage to [[Moses ben Jacob Cordovero]]'s ''[[Pardes Rimonim]]'', or "Pomegranate Orchard."

A third edition was printed in 1999, by Llewellyn Publications. This edition includes two introductions by Regardie, and one from [[Chic Cicero|Chic]] and [[Tabatha Cicero|Sandra Tabatha Cicero]]. The third edition is also furnished with a series of annotations done by the Ciceros, and an additional 320-page [[Hermetic Qabalah|qabalistic]] textbook, titled ''Skrying On The Tree of Life''. 

Regardie dedicates the book to [[Aleister Crowley]] and identifies the text as a theoretical introduction to the foundation of the magical work of the [[Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn]].

