'''Ave Maria lace''' is a [[lace]] manufactured until the mid-19th century, largely in [[Dieppe, Seine-Maritime|Dieppe]].<ref>http://fleurdandeol.com/french-lace.html</ref><ref>http://www.cs.arizona.edu/patterns/weaving/books/je_lace_3.pdf</ref> The lace is very narrow and was chiefly made by [[peasant]]s, from whom the name originates.{{what|date=June 2015}}

