{{Infobox music festival | music_festival_name = Black Sea Jazz Festival | image = | caption = | location = [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]: [[Batumi]], [[Black Sea Arena]] | years_active = 2007–present | founders = | dates = July | genre = Jazz, blues, soul, R&B, rock | website = {{URL|http://tbilisijazz.com/black-sea-jazz-festival-history/|Black Sea Jazz Festival}} }} The '''Black Sea Jazz Festival''' ({{lang-ka|შავი ზღვის ჯაზ-ფესტივალი}}) is an international [[jazz festival]] held annually, traditionally in July, in [[Batumi]] and nearby locations on [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]'s [[Black Sea]] coast, which, along with [[Tbilisi Jazz Festival]], is one of the country's main jazz events.
The festival was founded in 2007. The subsequent editions broadened the scope of the festival to include rock, R&B, soul, disco, funk, and hip-hop and hosted both Georgian and international performers as diverse as [[George Clinton (musician)|George Clinton]], [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Lisa Stansfield]], [[The Prodigy]], and [[Robert Plant]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Snoop Dogg, Lisa Stansfield to perform at Black Sea Jazz Festival|url=http://agenda.ge/news/32537/eng|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=Agenda.ge|date=31 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Quincy Jones, Lauryn Hill, Chris Brown among headliners for 2016 Black Sea Jazz Festival|url=http://agenda.ge/news/56954/eng|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=Agenda.ge|date=27 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sun, sea and sounds at the Black Sea Jazz Festival|url=http://www.euronews.com/2015/07/30/sun-sea-and-sounds-at-the-black-sea-jazz-festival/|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=Euronews|date=30 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Robert Plant opens Black Sea Jazz Festival in Georgia |url=http://agenda.ge/news/104391/eng |accessdate=31 July 2018 |work=Agenda.ge |date=20 July 2018}}</ref> The 10th edition, held from 15 to 24 July 2016, was the largest one in the history of the Black Sea Jazz Festival.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Karsaulidze|first1=Eka|title=10th Black Sea Jazz Festival to Host Unprecedented Number of Participants|url=http://georgiatoday.ge/news/3678/10th-Black-Sea-Jazz-Festival-to-Host-Unprecedented-Number-of-Participants|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=Georgia Today|date=28 April 2016}}</ref>
