{{Expand French|Tenture Les Chasses de Maximilien|date=July 2018}}
[[File:Hunt_of_Maximilian,_September,_Louvre.jpg|thumb|300px|''September - Scene from a deer hunt'']]
'''''Les Chasses de Maximilien''''' (''The Hunts of Maximilian'') or '''''Les Belles Chasses de Guise''''' (''The Beautiful Hunts of Guise'') is a set of twelve tapestries, each showing a different hunting scene symbolising a different month of the calendar. All the scenes are set in the [[Soignes Forest]] near [[Brussels]] and the tapestries were produced by a studio in that city. They were probably commissioned by a member of the [[House of Habsburg]] such as [[Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor|Charles V]], [[Margaret of Austria, Duchess of Savoy|Margaret of Austria]] or [[Mary of Hungary (governor of the Netherlands)|Mary of Hungary]] - the latter two both governed the [[Spanish Netherlands]] from Brussels.

