{{use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} {{DISPLAYTITLE:''The Joy of Science''}} [[File:TheJoyOfScience.jpg|thumb|right|200px|<center>DVD cover for ''"The Joy of Science"'' lecture series.</center>]]
'''''The Joy of Science''''' is a popular video and audio course series, consisting of 60 lectures, each 30 minutes long, presented by [[Robert Hazen|Dr. Robert Hazen]] of the [[George Mason University]] and the [[Carnegie Institution of Washington]]. The course, first introduced in 2001, is part of [[The Great Courses|The Great Courses (TGC)]] series, and is produced and distributed by [[The Teaching Company|The Teaching Company (TTC)]], located in [[Chantilly, Virginia]] in the [[United States]].<ref name="MicrobesMind">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Robert Hazen - Microbes/Mind Adviser |url=http://microbes-mind.net/advisers/#RobertHazen |date= |work=Microbes-Mind.net|accessdate=9 May 2018 }}</ref><ref name="KKFI-20140721">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Evolution of Life, Life In Outer Space |url=http://www.kkfi.org/program-episodes/evolution-of-life-life-in-outer-space/ |date=21 July 2014 |work=[[KKFI]] |accessdate=9 May 2018 }}</ref><ref name="NSTA-2012">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=NSTA 2012 National Conference on Science Education |url=http://static.nsta.org/pdfs/2012IndianapolisProgram1.pdf |format=[[PDF]] |date=2012 |work=[[National Science Teachers Association]] |accessdate=9 May 2018 |page=203}}</ref><ref name="ISO-2017">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Information Technology - Introduction |url=https://www.iso.org/obp/ui/fr/#iso:std:iso-iec:tr:20017:ed-1:v1:en |date=2017 |work=[[International Organization for Standardization]] |accessdate=9 May 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Kelly|first1=Kate|title=That's not in my science book a compilation of little-known facts|date=2006|publisher=Taylor Trade Publishing|location=Lanham|isbn=9781461636014|page=ix}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Millman|first1=Martine|last2=Millman|first2=Gregory|title=Homeschooling : a family's journey|date=2008|publisher=Penguin|isbn=9781440632310}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ceceri|first1=Kathy|title=Integrated Science at Home: The Joy of Science|url=http://integratedscienceathome.blogspot.com/2010/11/joy-of-science.html|website=Integrated Science at Home|accessdate=12 May 2018|date=3 November 2010}}</ref>
== Background == [[File:Dr. Robert Hazen.jpg|thumb|left|200px|<center>[[Robert Hazen|Dr. Robert Hazen]]</center>]]
As the Clarence B. Robinson Professor at [[George Mason University]], [[Robert Hazen]] developed innovative courses to promote [[scientific literacy]] in both scientists and non-scientists.<ref name=DistinguishedPresentation>{{cite journal|last1=Hemley|first1=R. J.|title=Presentation of the Distinguished Public Service Medal of the Mineralogical Society of America for 2009|journal=American Mineralogist|date=25 March 2010|volume=95|issue=4|pages=666–666|doi=10.2138/am.2010.557|bibcode=2010AmMin..95..666H}}</ref> In a collaboration with physicist [[James Trefil]], he wrote three undergraduate textbooks: ''The Sciences: An Integrated Approach'' (1993),<ref>{{cite book|last1=Trefil|first1=James|last2=Hazen|first2=Robert M.|title=The sciences : an integrated approach|date=1994|publisher=Wiley|location=New York|isbn=978-0471303008|edition=A preliminary}}</ref> ''The Physical Sciences: An Integrated Approach'' (1995),<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hazen|first1=Robert M.|last2=Trefil|first2=James|title=The Physical science : an integrated approach|date=1996|publisher=Wiley|location=New York|isbn=9780471002499}}</ref> and ''Physics Matters: An Introduction to Conceptual Physics'' (2004).<ref>{{cite book|last1=Trefil|first1=James|last2=Hazen|first2=Robert M.|title=Physics matter : an introduction to conceptual physics|date=2004|publisher=J. Wiley|isbn=9780471150589}}</ref> Hazen used these as the basis for a 60-lecture video and audio course called ''The Joy of Science''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Robert Hazen|url=https://robinsonprofessors.gmu.edu/about/robert-hazen/|website=Robinson Professors|publisher=George Mason University|accessdate=13 May 2018|date=8 October 2010}}</ref><ref name=DistinguishedPresentation/> {{clear}}
